title: Sooner Stampede
description:
Race #1 of the Tour de Dirt presented by GEAX, Oklahoma\'s State XC Mountain Bike Championship Series.  For additional rules and regulations for the TdD, see
www.tourdedirt.org. For information contact, Gregg Grosshans at 405-837-0265
course: Course Description: Approximately 9 mile lap consisting of 90% single track. Short climbs with fast flowing sections.
registration: On-line registration open until 3/17.  Race day registration available for $5 (no late fee for Jr\'s).  Kids Kup registration race day only.  Race day registration will end 30 minutes prior to the start of your race!  Tour de Dirt (TdD) number plate will be required to participate in any TdD event in 2013.  This is a one time $5 charge.  These number plates are available for sale at any TdD event.   This is your number plate for the entire 2013 season so don\'t lose it.  Racers must show their 2013 TdD number plate before they will be allowed to register/race at the Sooner Stampede.
notes: Free Kids race starts at 10:00 am. Training wheels, 4-6, 7-9 & 10-12 age categories.
directions:
Lake Thunderbird State Park, Clear Bay Area
SH-9 East, 13 miles east of I-35, Norman, OK

title: Tour de Trykes Twilght Criterium
description:
Course follows a route through downtown Enid, eight turns with a moderate uphill, and a flat finish. Course 
direction is a figure eight which is fast and tight.
course: Race course is a figure 8 with 8 turns with one uphill and a flat finish in downtown Enid Oklahoma.
registration:
Registration opens at 4:00pm, Pre registration @ USA Cycling.org. Online registration will end at 11pm CDT on 8/15/2013. On site entry will close 15 minutes prior to the start of each race and the entry fee will increase day of by $10.00. Riders must present a valid USA Cycling racing license. One day license available $10.00 at registration for Cat 5 men and 
Cat 4 women. A portion of the entry fee goes to BRAOK for tech support and USAC for insurance surcharges.
notes:
Awards for the first three finishers will be held immediately after the finish of the race. Free lap rule will be in effect. Wheels in/wheels out pit. Helmets must be worn while on the bike.  All posted prizes to be paid in cash. Lapped riders may be pulled. Minimum field is 4. Awards to first 3 finishers immediately at the 
conclusion of their event. Race results will be reported to USAC for ranking purposes. Race held rain or shine!
directions: from the north on I-35 exit Hwy 412 west to Enid. From south I-35 exit Hwy 412 west to Enid, north on Independence St to course. Parking available on the perimeter of the course.

title: Oklahoma Short Track MTB State Championships
TNCX Practice
description: Cyclocross Practice Series- Bring your bike out to the west bank skate park, and shred around for a while! Get better! Have a beer! Every Tuesday in September, October, and a few in November. Guaranteed not to disappoint, but may hurt a little.
course: Courses will vary from week to week to include different aspects of cyclocross. These may be sand, run-ups, tight turns, and the occasional barrier (count on these being out more than occasionally)! These events are held on the west bank of Tulsa Riverparks near the skate park just South of the 23rd street bridge!
registration: Registration is 5$ per rider, and 10$ if you don't have a USAC licensee. I am hoping to have a card reader up and running by the first event so that you can now pay with plastic. Also a discounted rate if you choose to pay for the entire practice series up-front!
notes: Start times are tentative each week for the kids, B, and A races. The C race will start each week promptly at 5:25 so as to allow time to race before the sun sets!

title: Lake Murraython Weekend
description: This is a dirt omnium/stage race awarding winners based on total time to complete all stages.
course:
Ultra marathon dirt/gravel roads course between 100k-200k at promoter\'s discretion. Course may be modified at any time.

Ultra marathon mtb trail at Lake Murray State Park utilizing multiple laps to total a MINIMUM of 100K. Course TBD. Singletrack MTB may be diverted to another dirt/gravel roads loop based on weather.
